### Purpose
Define named rectangular regions; cut from `default` or another frame. Attach a `page` or use for styling.

### Options
- `page <name>` — set child page (RMF file without extension).
- `cpage <cvar>` — page name read from console variable.
- `cut <name>` — cut this frame from an existing frame.
- `border <width> <lineWidth> <lineColour>` — inner border.
- `backfill <colour>` — fill color for frames without a page.

### Notes
- Frames scale with resolution; `default` covers the full page (or resized area).

### Example
```text
<frame sidebar 160 480 cut default backfill 0x60000000>
<frame content 480 480 cut default page m_video>
```

